Which literary device is used here for the word “burned” and “dry”, “Summer burned the canals dry.”?
It’s a very simple metaphor. The writer could have said “The summer SUN burned the canals dry” and the sentence would not be metaphoric. Saying that summer is LIKE the sun makes this a metaphor. It’s comparing summer to the sun without saying it.


