✓ Never fall for this optician trick if you feel eye strain on Mobile or Laptop

So you work for long hours in front of laptop or mobile phone.

One day you decide to buy a pair of blue light blocking eyeglasses and visit an optician.

He shows you lens test experiment with a laser torch which emits blue light.

He points blue laser beam on the lenses and you see that the laser beam can’t pass through the clear lenses.

You become happy and buy those lenses.

But wait.

You are completely unaware that clear lenses do not block much blue light.

Then what about the laser test that optician did?

Such laser pens actually emit Violet light and not blue light

Clear lenses can never block much blue light.

Why do people get tricked with laser test on clear lenses ?



Blue and Violet colors are somewhat similar in appearance. People usually do not notice the difference (in the absence of comparison like above).

Then how to block the harsh screen light ?

As per the scientific research[1] only amber lenses can block real blue light and is beneficial for computer & mobile users.

The shade of amber lenses is a blend of yellow-orange.

Edit, Folks, Please don’t send personal message to ask about which brand of computer glasses to buy.

In my opinion there are 2 good brands. Gunnar (in usa) and Zebriana (in India). They both follow amber technology in computer glasses.

Do your own research before buying and alert others about laser trick.

