What is the saddest truth about life?
1. You will not necessarily succeed if you try, but you will not succeed if you do not try.

2. The world is never fair.

And the difference between people and people is greater than even the difference between people and dogs.

3. Appearance is power.

Good-looking people always have access to more facilities and benefits.

4. All roads lead to Rome, but some people are born in Rome.

Family conditions are a very important factor in any decision you make at a young age. We fight tooth and nail to live what (in some people's eyes) is an ordinary life.



5. Discrimination is really everywhere.

Gender, race, religion, province, even the color of the skin (nationality). People are born with the attribute of rejecting the other, cultivated people will restrain, but sometimes deep-seated prejudice, it is really difficult to avoid.

6. The people who will feel happy for your happiness and sadness for your sadness are very few. And others, regardless of affinity, are more willing to see you living wrose than they are.

7. The people who value relationship over interests are rare, but there are still some, if you are lucky enough to encounter them, cherish them.

8. Sometimes two people are each other's Plan B, but also pretend that the other one is their only beloved person in the wedding.

9. The cruel truth is that everyone knows the truth, but they have to join together to whitewash it.

10. There is a cool side of life, but also a warm side. And some other things are actually very neutral, not good or bad.

Your life only belongs to you. It is what you think it is. We should learn to discover more of the sunshine in life.




