When teaching Basic Electronics to new recruits I used the analogy of water in a pipe where,

The pipe = Conductor

Pressure = Voltage

Flow Rate = Amperage

Valve = Resistor

Diaphragm Pressure Can = Capacitance

I never was able to come up with an accurate and effective analogy for inductance though, but even with that lack it was a very effective teaching tool for the core basics of electricity (and for safety issues).

We all know almost intuitively that a 9 to 12 psig water jet isn't a problem but a 120 or 240 psig hose absolutely is a problem.



