I would recommend that you watch movies that you've already watched in your own native language. That way you already know the story, and can concentrate on listening to the English. Therefore, the film should be in English without any subtitles. Watch it once all the way through paying close attention to it. Then, watch it again concentrating on different scenes and repeating them as many times as needed until you understand them completely. Then, watch the movie again taking notes of the things you've learned. Finally, watch it again just for fun and whenever possible try to say the lines of the characters with them.

