Delivery is choppy, fragmented,
or telegraphic. Speech
contains frequent pauses and
hesitations. Range and control of grammar
and vocabulary severely limit (or
prevent) expression of ideas and
connections among ideas. Some
very low-level responses may
rely on isolated words or short
utterances to communicate
ideas. The response fails to provide
much relevant content. Ideas
that are expressed are often
inaccurate, limited to vague
utterances, or repetitions
(including repetition of prompt).
